source.name: ENERGY STAR Labeled Buildings and Plants
source.description: ENERGY STAR Labeled Buildings and Plants is a publically available EPA database of facilities that have earned the ENERGY STAR for use of prudent energy management strategies and proven technologies in managing and operating commercial and industrial facilities. ENERGY STAR is a joint program of the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency and the U.S. Department of Energy helping us all save money and protect the environment through energy efficient products and practices.
